<!doctype html>
<meta charset="utf-8"><link rel="stylesheet" href="gallery.css">
<div class="stack" style="width:100%">
	<h2>You control what happens on release</h2>
	<div class="timeline">
		<!-- The hold runs until after the before-release tap has landed — that overlap is
		     the whole point of having two slots, so the diagram has to show it. -->
		<div class="hold">hold combination held down</div>

		<div class="tap" style="left:700px; top:24px">before release</div>
		<div class="tick" style="left:840px; top:100px; height:16px"></div>

		<div class="tick" style="left:1020px; top:100px; height:130px"></div>
		<div class="note" style="left:1034px; top:214px">hold released</div>

		<div class="pause" style="left:1044px; top:159px; width:150px"></div>
		<div class="tap" style="left:1214px; top:124px">after release</div>
	</div>
	<p style="max-width:1680px">Tap a second hotkey <b>before</b> letting go — while the hold
	is still down — <b>after</b> it, or both. A pause either side gives a fussy app time to
	notice. Use either, both, or neither.</p>
</div>